                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/193.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Peru</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Argentina answered Peruvian inquiry respecting new negotiations with Chile.
                    Declined giving advice. Brazil advised to seize offer<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1561fn1">Made by Mr. Alfonso, the Chilean agent.</note> to divide
                    territory in dispute and cautiously offered moral support. I think Peru is
                    inclined to negotiate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Combs</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
